{"key":"processedPost-19454299","value":{"id":19454299,"first":19454088,"last":19455299,"when":1390354762,"utime":"01/22/14 03:39 AM","content":"You don't need a hygrometer.&nbsp; The humidity in the air is irrelevant.&nbsp; The humidity at the pinning surface of your cakes is what matters and this is why we mist a few times daily.&nbsp; Misting replaces the moisture which naturally evaporates from the substrates as a result of the fresh air exchange.&nbsp; This ebb and flow of moisture content is a major pinning trigger.<br /><br />The overspray from misting keeps the perlite damp, so it should never dry out during the growing cycle.<br />RR","title":"Re: Low RH? Advise?"}}